Unitized curtain walls are pre-assembled in a factory and then shipped to the job site, while stick built curtain walls are constructed on site piece by piece. In general, unitized curtain walls are more expensive than stick built curtain walls, but they are also faster and easier to install.



Unitized curtain walls making up the majority of the market. This is due to the fact that unitized curtain walls offer many advantages over stick built curtain walls, including faster installation times and reduced labor costs.



There is also a small portion of the market share occupied by custom curtain walls. Custom curtain walls are designed and built to meet the specific needs of a project, and as such they are usually more expensive than either unitized or stick built curtain walls. However, custom curtain walls can offer unique benefits that make them worth the extra cost in some cases.

